5.1.
The apps are as of now available on Android and iOS. The Scanbooster Ultrasound Sim app (the simulator) allows the simulation of sonography and contains a learning diary, an exam mode as well as labeling and a changing number of individual organ-volumes. The simulator is intended to work on a tablet or smartphone. The Scanbooster Control app (control app) allows controlling the simulator by moving the smartphone around, creating the feeling of the smartphone being a "virtual ultrasound probe".
5.2.
No liability of any kind is assumed by Scanbooster that the apps run on any of the intended devices.
5.3.
Scanbooster reserves the right to change, remove, add and or modify features stated under 5.1. This may happen without prior notice and without prior consent of the user. Also the user is not entitled to receive compensation of any kind when such actions are taken by Scanbooster.
